reviews.text:
Wonderful Northern-style Thai restaurant!
The owner was welcoming and kind. The food flavors were bold and deeply satisfying.
Every dish I tried had its own personality. What really impressed me was learning that they import key ingredients directly from Thailand.
If you are looking for something beyond the usual Pad Thai and Green Curry, this place is a must-visit.

Crispy Tofu and Thai District Wings were cooked perfectly - amazing crispy exterior with juicy interior. Spices and flavors were spot on throughout. Shrimp Pad Thai was solid, shrimp cooked with great attention to detail. Flavors were rich and full but maybe slightly on the sweet side. Shows they really know how to handle their proteins here.

Thai District is top notch! Not only is it a beautiful place, the food is incredible. I got the pot stickers and drunken noodles, my go to comfort food whenever I order Thai cuisine.

These dishes at Thai District were top notch! Beautifully cooked and very flavorful. All of the staff are very kind and the service was great! Definitely give Thai District a try!

I ordered many times from this place and the food was always very solid. This is the first time I went there for dessert. I had never had the dessert before. It was totally worth it. The chef has been apparently trained in France. The Churros were fresh and crispy and the souffle is to die for.

Porkbelly was the best. Ordered a level 3 on spice for my drunken noodles.... very hot! It took forever to get our food. The waiter forgot 1 dish and by the time it was brought to our table, we were finished dining. Nice ambiance.

editorial_summary.overview: Understated setting for a menu of primarily Northern Thai dishes, plus drinks.

Our male server never introduced himself, snatched the menus from our hands, and dropped off our food missing the Jasmine rice we had ordered. We had to ask the female server for help instead, but her approach was neither warm nor welcoming.

Later, we waited ten minutes before flagging her down again, but she never returned with the check, which left us having to pay at the front. Once there, we still had to wait another three to four minutes before anyone helped us. Meanwhile, a nearby table used the f-word almost every other sentence, which added to the underwhelming dinner experience.

The only reason this isn‚Äôt a one-star review is because of the atmosphere and vibe upstairs, which was enjoyable. Unfortunately, we won‚Äôt be back to dine in and will instead stick to curbside pickup at the second Thai District location at Partake Kitchen.

Even if the food wasn't spicy hot eniugh for me, the quality was definitely there. The pork belly is to die for... will be going there again, soon. By the way, the place is absolutely lovely...upstairs, a must go there... with a date...
Tonight, I came with my son and we both love the Golden Bags and the Thai District Dumpling which are absolutely delicious. The most important was to eat the famous Giang Hung- Lay Northern Style. It's pork belly and pork loin in the most delicious tamarind, ginger, garlic, peanuts and more good things sauce. It is divine. My only regret was  too much pork loin and not enough pork belly... my son and I love this pork belly dish,but it was lacking of it. He had none and I had two pieces. Perhaps next time we will make sure it is more belly and less loin... üòâ
Nevertheless, it was delicious... the mango sticky rice was lovely, also.
See you soon.

detailedReviews.author: Harvey
detailedReviews.text:
Most of the dishes here are from northern Thailand and include dishes besides the normal pad Thai and red curries.
I would recommend the Nam Kao Tod salad, duck curry and drunken pork ragu. Everyone at the table raved about those dishes.
The service was great, but I would definitely make a reservation to avoid the long wait for walk ins (A better table management would cut down on the wait times significantly.). Didn‚Äôt get the chance to see the patio, but eating inside with the nice decor is the way to do it.
Finish off dinner with sticky rice and mango. Your waistline won‚Äôt thank me, but your tastebuds will.

detailedReviews.author: Jordan Taylor
detailedReviews.text: Honestly, one of the best experiences I have ever had in the United States when it comes to Thai food. My food was hot delicious and came out so fast after I ordered. The drinks were also very yummy. I cannot recommend this place highly enough!

detailedReviews.text: Really great service. The Panang curry was perfect not watery or overly thick but blended very well. Good kick on the thai spicy level. The wings for appetizers was also great. detailedReviews.text:
If you‚Äôre a lover of Thai Food Thai District is a must try!!!  The Food, Atmosphere and Service is top tier excellence. This is one of my favorite places to eat in Long Beach. My Favorite Dishes are
Chicken or Vegetable Pad Thai
Chicken or Vegetable Drunken Noodles
Garlic and Pepper Chicken

detailedReviews.author: Mark Quidem
detailedReviews.text: If you're looking for good Thai food, look no further than that district. The food tasted great and authentic. Service was quick and friendly when I went for lunch. If nothing else, go for the mango sticky rice, always a favorite.

detailedReviews.author: Emerson S
detailedReviews.text:
Went in with a party of 5 at 8:30pm with no reservation. They were able to make us wait for no longer than 15 mins and took us in . Best food ever . Everyone was really nice and we were treated well.
Spicy fried rice and drunken noodles mild were our favorites . The mango dessert was delicious.
Also I would like to point out that prices are extremely reasonable and nothing seemed overpriced like other places nowadays.
We will be coming back .
